&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equinox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equinox&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It refers to a day with an equal duration of day and night.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;There are two equinoxes in a year:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;March 21&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;( Vernal Equinox)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;September 23&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;( Autumnal Equinox)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is the time when the sun is nearest to the equatorial plane which provides equal lengths of day and night.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solstice&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;It is the time of the year when the sun is farthest from the equatorial giving the long days or nights.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It happens twice a year&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;

	&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Summer Solstice ( June 21)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Winter Solstice( December 22)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aphelion&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is the point of Earth&amp;#39;s orbit that is farthest from the Sun.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It happens in early July.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perihelion&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;It is the point of the Earth&amp;#39;s orbit that is nearest to the Sun.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It happens in early January.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sam Manekshaw&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;was&lt;strong&gt; the first army officer of Independent India&lt;/strong&gt; to be&amp;nbsp;conferred the rank of &lt;strong&gt;Field Marshal.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He was the &lt;strong&gt;Indian Army&amp;#39;s Chief of Staff during the 1971 Indo-Pakistani War.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;His military career spanned four decades and five wars, beginning with service in&lt;strong&gt; World War II for the British Indian Army.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He had been awarded the Military Cross for gallantry in World War II.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Om Prakash Malhotra &lt;/strong&gt;was the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;13th chief of Army Staff &lt;/strong&gt;of the Indian Army.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gopal Gurunath Bewoor&lt;/strong&gt; was&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the 9th chief of Army Staff&lt;/strong&gt; of the Indian Army.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &lt;u&gt;9 January.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pravasi Bharatiya Divas (PBD)&lt;/strong&gt; is celebrated on &lt;strong&gt;9&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; January&lt;/strong&gt; every year to mark the contribution of the &lt;strong&gt;Overseas Indian community&lt;/strong&gt; to the development of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;January 9 was chosen as the day to celebrate this occasion since it was &lt;strong&gt;on this day in 1915 that Ma&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;hatma Gandhi returned to India from South Africa.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pravasi Bharatiya Divas (PBD)&lt;/strong&gt; conventions are&lt;strong&gt; being held every year since 2003.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;16&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; Pravasi Bharatiya Divas &lt;/strong&gt;Convention was&amp;nbsp;inaugurated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi on &lt;strong&gt;9 January 2021&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;17th&lt;/strong&gt; Pravasi Bharatiya Divas&amp;nbsp;Convention will be held from&lt;strong&gt; 8 &amp;ndash; 10 January 2023&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;Indore&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Madhya Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; theme&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;17th&lt;/strong&gt; PBD is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Diaspora: Reliable Partners for India&amp;#39;s Progress in Amrit Kaal&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

